          "insert": "nullable by design",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — this is the dock spec's \"modal relinquishing\" rule (fj-053 onward): no dock button shows active/violet while the Shapes panel or another surface owns focus. The consuming editor must derive this prop from the current interaction mode, not from \"last tool used\"; the dock itself must never track sticky/last-selected state internally. Separately, "
        },
        {
          "insert": "onSelectTool(tool)",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " fires for every button including "
        },
        {
          "insert": "\"shapes\"",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", while "
        },
        {
          "insert": "onOpenShapes()",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " fires in addition for that one button — a consumer may keep both effects or treat "
        },
        {
          "insert": "onOpenShapes",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " as the sole handler, since the component fires both. The "
        },
        {
          "insert": "ToolId",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " union intentionally excludes "
        },
        {
          "insert": "\"overflow\"",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (handled instead by "
        },
        {
          "insert": "onOpenOverflow",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "), since the \"+\" button is not a \"tool\" in the schema sense."
